// Dymo LabelWriter consumables registry — paper rolls and D1 tape
// cassettes alike. One entry per physical product (regional / durable /
// count-per-roll SKU variants collapse onto one entry via the `skus`
// array). Per-`type` rules below.
//
// ─── Paper (`type: 'die-cut' | 'continuous'`) ─────────────────────
//
// Sourced from the official Dymo per-printer compatibility matrix
// (`dymo-labels-lw.pdf`, archived at the repo root). One entry per
// physical (widthMm × heightMm).
//
// Dimensions assume the 300-dpi print engine (11.81 dots per mm);
// `lengthDots = round(heightMm * 11.81)` is kept on each die-cut
// entry so the 550-series status parser can round-trip its dot-based
// response to a friendly mm descriptor.
//
// Rectangular die-cut entries declare `defaultOrientation: 'horizontal'`
// — users author landscape (long axis horizontal as you read it), and
// the driver auto-rotates 90° CW so the visual reads along the tape
// feed direction. Pre-retrofit, landscape input was silently cropped
// to head width; the auto-rotate path fixes that.
//
// Every paper entry carries `targetModels: ['lw']` (fits any LW paper
// engine) except wide-only rolls, which carry `['lw-wide']` and only
// match engines that declare the wide tier (LW 4XL / 5XL).
//
// `printMargins` is intentionally **omitted**. The 1.5 mm "design-tool
// inset" we used to encode here was uniform across every entry —
// strong signal it isn't actually media-specific. The real,
// useful margins are the chassis-physical leading / trailing /
// side offsets, which vary per *engine*, not per *media*. Those
// live on `engines[].capabilities.{leadingEdgeOffsetMm, ...}`
// (currently populated for LW_330_TURBO; see
// plans/backlog/chassis-offset-and-pitch-semantics.md). Design
// tools that want a visual-breathing-room inset should layer their
// own constant on top of the chassis offset.
//
// `cornerRadiusMm` is informational; previews use it to render the
// actual paper outline.
//
// `key` on each entry is the lookup name exposed via `MEDIA[key]` —
// e.g. `MEDIA.ADDRESS_STANDARD`. The compile-data script folds this
// array into a keyed-by-`key` map at build time.

[
  // ─── address ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  {
    key: 'RETURN_ADDRESS',
    id: 'return-address',
    name: '19×51mm Return Address',
    category: 'address',
    widthMm: 19,
    heightMm: 51,
    type: 'die-cut',
    defaultOrientation: 'horizontal',
    cornerRadiusMm: 3,
    lengthDots: 602,
    skus: ['30330', '30578'],
    targetModels: ['lw'],
  },
  {
    key: 'ADDRESS_STANDARD',
    id: 'address-standard',
    name: '89×28mm Address',
    category: 'address',
    widthMm: 28,
    heightMm: 89,
    type: 'die-cut',
    defaultOrientation: 'horizontal',
    cornerRadiusMm: 3,
    lengthDots: 1051,
    skus: ['30251', '30252', '30254', '30320', '30340'],
